==English==
===Etymology===
From the Greek word plethein, which means "to be full".

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-plethora.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
'''plethora''' (''used in the phrase'' '''a plethora of''')
#An excessive [[amount]] or [[number]]; an [[abundance]].
#:''The menu offers a '''plethora''' of cuisines from around the world.''
#:''El Guapo had a '''plethora''' of piñatas.''

====Synonyms====
*(1): [[excess]], [[glut]], [[surfeit]], [[superfluity]], [[slew]]


